{
  "stem": "10572.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But when we ultimately were on our way to Buchenwald, my father said to me, he said, you know, Fritz, you and I are probably the only ones who know what we can look forward to if it is true what [?",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Nilsen ?] told us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And our car was parked in front of our house and was a new car.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they said, in order to get us home faster, we should take our car.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was naive enough to sit behind the wheel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said, get in the back of the car.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I drive the car, one of the SS men said.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was the last time we saw the car.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we went to Gestapo headquarters.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And on the way, as we got closer to Gestapo headquarters-- it was still dark-- we saw, like, ghosts, people, other people, friends of ours, on their way to Gestapo headquarters.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And among them was a quite famous physician, who was a very famous ear, nose, and throat specialist, [GERMAN] Dr.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Krebs, whose son later on won the Nobel Prize in biochemistry.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And by this time, we knew it was not just us who were arrested.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was a mass action.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And early in the morning, all of us were taken to the prison, and-- the local prison, and then lined up-- lined up outside the prison, 75 of us, to be taken on a march through the city, through the streets of our city.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And across the street-- across the street from the police headquarters was the chamber of commerce.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And there were people standing at the windows and kind of laughing, but not a happy laugh, kind of an embarrassed laugh seeing this sad little group of Jews down there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And that was probably, to the people up there, an anonymous group.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They didn't know who they were.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Except that among the people that were standing there, I saw a girl who used to be my partner in dancing school, a girl-- blond girl Margaret [INAUDIBLE], who looked out.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I stared at her.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I somehow think that there was a hypnosis that made our eyes meet.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the moment she discovered me, the group was not anonymous anymore.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She saw somebody that she knew.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And she stopped laughing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And she turned around and walked away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I never saw her again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I thought it was one of the symbolic, very, very interesting things, that you can talk about 'the Jews,' but the moment you know somebody specifically in there, it becomes intolerable for the viewer.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And we were taken then-- now, marched through the streets.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And the SS had unlocked their guns.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we were told that any attempt to move out of line without any warning, we would be shot.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And we were taken around the streets of our city.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And there were people standing on the sidewalks, and I think some of them in horror, looking at this scenario.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And when we finally moved down on the street, there was a whisper among us, that only was a rumor we couldn't believe.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But the direction that this march took, it looked like we were going to our synagogue.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And little by little, we got close enough that we could smell the burn.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we were taken around our burning synagogue, marched around the burning synagogue.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the SS-- or the SR, whoever it was-- had taken a Torah roll out and rolled it out on the street and made us march across the Torah rolls.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we were then taken-- after this march de triomphe, we were taken back.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And we were split up because we were too many to be taken to one prison.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We were taken to two different prisons.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "In the middle of the next night, we were loaded on open trucks.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I was still with my father.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In fact, there's another, if I can-- but my-- so we went to-- we were loaded on open trucks and taken in the November night.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Many of them in-- only in their pajamas with an overcoat over it, without being dressed properly.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were taken [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] away from Hildesheim.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We didn't know where we were going.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were going to Hanover.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in Hanover, there was a special train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were loaded on the special train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And on this special train were Jews from surrounding villages near Hanover, among them from Pattensen, the birthplace of my father.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my uncle, with his two sons, were also on the train.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In the-- while we were on the train-- and still didn't know yet where we were going, and one of the worst punishments and greatest fear was this uncertainty.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
